      [32m"content[0m"[33m:[0m [32m"<p align=[0m\"center[0m\">[0m\n  <img src=[0m\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/likhonsheikhdev/docker-model-runner/main/assets/logo.svg[0m\" width=[0m\"200[0m\" alt=[0m\"Docker Model Runner Logo[0m\">[0m\n</p>[0m\n[0m\n<h1 align=[0m\"center[0m\">Docker Model Runner</h1>[0m\n[0m\n<p align=[0m\"center[0m\">[0m\n  <strong>Self-hosted Anthropic API Compatible Inference Server</strong>[0m\n</p>[0m\n[0m\n<p align=[0m\"center[0m\">[0m\n  <a href=[0m\"#features[0m\">Features</a> •[0m\n  <a href=[0m\"#quick-start[0m\">Quick Start</a> •[0m\n  <a href=[0m\"#claude-code-integration[0m\">Claude Code</a> •[0m\n  <a href=[0m\"#api-reference[0m\">API Reference</a> •[0m\n  <a href=[0m\"#deployment[0m\">Deployment</a>[0m\n</p>[0m\n[0m\n<p align=[0m\"center[0m\">[0m\n  <img src=[0m\"https://img.shields.io/badge/Anthropic_API-Compatible-blueviolet?style=for-the-badge[0m\" alt=[0m\"Anthropic Compatible[0m\">[0m\n  <img src=[0m\"https://img.shields.io/badge/OpenAI_API-Compatible-green?style=for-the-badge[0m\" alt=[0m\"OpenAI Compatible[0m\">[0m\n  <img src=[0m\"https://img.shields.io/badge/Docker-Ready-2496ED?style=for-the-badge&logo=docker[0m\" alt=[0m\"Docker Ready[0m\">[0m\n  <img src=[0m\"https://img.shields.io/badge/HuggingFace-Spaces-yellow?style=for-the-badge&logo=huggingface[0m\" alt=[0m\"HuggingFace[0m\">[0m\n</p>[0m\n[0m\n<p align=[0m\"center[0m\">[0m\n  <img src=[0m\"https://img.shields.io/github/license/likhonsheikhdev/docker-model-runner?style=flat-square[0m\" alt=[0m\"License[0m\">[0m\n  <img src=[0m\"https://img.shields.io/github/stars/likhonsheikhdev/docker-model-runner?style=flat-square[0m\" alt=[0m\"Stars[0m\">[0m\n  <img src=[0m\"https://img.shields.io/badge/python-3.11+-blue?style=flat-square[0m\" alt=[0m\"Python[0m\">[0m\n  <a href=[0m\"https://t.me/likhonsheikh[0m\"><img src=[0m\"https://img.shields.io/badge/Telegram-@likhonsheikh-2CA5E0?style=flat-square&logo=telegram[0m\" alt=[0m\"Telegram[0m\"></a>[0m\n</p>[0m\n[0m\n<p align=[0m\"center[0m\">[0m\n  <strong>Author:</strong> <a href=[0m\"https://github.com/likhonsheikhdev[0m\">Likhon Sheikh</a>[0m\n  &nbsp;|&nbsp;[0m\n  <a href=[0m\"https://t.me/likhonsheikh[0m\">[0m\n    <img src=[0m\"https://img.shields.io/badge/Contact-Telegram-blue?logo=telegram[0m\" alt=[0m\"Telegram[0m\" height=[0m\"20[0m\">[0m\n  </a>[0m\n</p>[0m\n[0m\n---[0m\n[0m\n## Overview[0m\n[0m\n**Docker Model Runner** is a production-ready, self-hosted API server that provides full compatibility with the **Anthropic Messages API**. It enables you to run local language models while maintaining compatibility with tools like **Claude Code**, **Cursor**, and other AI-powered development tools.[0m\n[0m\n### Why Docker Model Runner?[0m\n[0m\n- **Drop-in Replacement**: Works seamlessly with any tool expecting Anthropic's API[0m\n- **Claude Code Compatible**: Use with Claude Code CLI for AI-assisted development[0m\n- **Interleaved Thinking**: Full support for extended thinking with streaming[0m\n- **Multi-API Support**: Both Anthropic and OpenAI API formats supported[0m\n- **CPU Optimized**: Runs efficiently on CPU-only hardware (2 vCPU, 16GB RAM)[0m\n- **Zero Configuration**: Deploy to HuggingFace Spaces with one click[0m\n[0m\n---[0m\n[0m\n## Features[0m\n[0m\n| Feature | Status |[0m\n|---------|--------|[0m\n| Anthropic Messages API (`/v1/messages`) | ✅ Full Support |[0m\n| OpenAI Chat Completions (`/v1/chat/completions`) | ✅ Full Support |[0m\n| Streaming (SSE) | ✅ Full Support |[0m\n| Interleaved Thinking | ✅ Full Support |[0m\n| Tool/Function Calling | ✅ Full Support |[0m\n| Multi-turn Conversations | ✅ Full Support |[0m\n| System Prompts | ✅ Full Support |[0m\n| CORS (Agentic Tools) | ✅ Enabled |[0m\n[0m\n---[0m\n[0m\n## Quick Start[0m\n[0m\n### Option 1: Use Hosted Version[0m\n[0m\n```bash[0m\n# Set environment variables[0m\nexport ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL=https://likhonsheikhdev-docker-model-runner.hf.space[0m\nexport ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=your-api-key[0m\n[0m\n# Use with Anthropic SDK[0m\npip install anthropic[0m\n```[0m\n[0m\n```python[0m\nimport anthropic[0m\n[0m\nclient = anthropic.Anthropic()[0m\n[0m\nmessage = client.messages.create([0m\n    model=[0m\"claude-sonnet-4-20250514[0m\",[0m\n    max_tokens=1024,[0m\n    messages=[{[0m\"role[0m\": [0m\"user[0m\", [0m\"content[0m\": [0m\"Hello![0m\"}][0m\n)[0m\n[0m\nprint(message.content[0].text)[0m\n```[0m\n[0m\n### Option 2: Self-Host with Docker[0m\n[0m\n```bash[0m\n# Clone the repository[0m\ngit clone https://github.com/likhonsheikhdev/docker-model-runner.git[0m\ncd docker-model-runner[0m\n[0m\n# Build and run[0m\ndocker build -t model-runner .[0m\ndocker run -p 7860:7860 model-runner[0m\n```[0m\n[0m\n### Option 3: Deploy to HuggingFace Spaces[0m\n[0m\n1. Fork this repository[0m\n2. Create a new Space on HuggingFace with Docker SDK[0m\n3. Upload the files[0m\n4. Your API is ready at `https://your-username-space-name.hf.space`[0m\n[0m\n---[0m\n[0m\n## Claude Code Integration[0m\n[0m\nUse Docker Model Runner as your Claude Code backend:[0m\n[0m\n### 1. Install Claude Code[0m\n[0m\n```bash[0m\n# NPM[0m\nnpm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code[0m\n[0m\n# Homebrew (macOS)[0m\nbrew install --cask claude-code[0m\n[0m\n# Direct install[0m\ncurl -fsSL https://claude.ai/install.sh | bash[0m\n```[0m\n[0m\n### 2. Configure Settings[0m\n[0m\nCreate `~/.claude/settings.json`:[0m\n[0m\n```json[0m\n{[0m\n  [0m\"env[0m\": {[0m\n    [0m\"ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL[0m\": [0m\"https://likhonsheikhdev-docker-model-runner.hf.space[0m\",[0m\n    [0m\"ANTHROPIC_API_KEY[0m\": [0m\"your-api-key[0m\",[0m\n    [0m\"API_TIMEOUT_MS[0m\": [0m\"300000[0m\"[0m\n  },[0m\n  [0m\"model[0m\": [0m\"claude-sonnet-4-20250514[0m\",[0m\n  [0m\"smallFastModel[0m\": [0m\"claude-sonnet-4-20250514[0m\"[0m\n}[0m\n```[0m\n[0m\n### 3. Run Claude Code[0m\n[0m\n```bash[0m\nclaude[0m\n```[0m\n[0m\n---[0m\n[0m\n## Interleaved Thinking[0m\n[0m\nEnable reasoning chains interleaved with responses:[0m\n[0m\n```python[0m\nimport anthropic[0m\n[0m\nclient = anthropic.Anthropic([0m\n    base_url=[0m\"https://likhonsheikhdev-docker-model-runner.hf.space[0m\"[0m\n)[0m\n[0m\nmessage = client.messages.create([0m\n    model=[0m\"claude-sonnet-4-20250514[0m\",[0m\n    max_tokens=2048,[0m\n    thinking={[0m\n        [0m\"type[0m\": [0m\"enabled[0m\",[0m\n        [0m\"budget_tokens[0m\": 500[0m\n    },[0m\n    messages=[{[0m\"role[0m\": [0m\"user[0m\", [0m\"content[0m\": [0m\"Solve: What is 15% of 240?[0m\"}][0m\n)[0m\n[0m\nfor block in message.content:[0m\n    if block.type == [0m\"thinking[0m\":[0m\n        print(f[0m\"💭 Thinking: {block.thinking}[0m\")[0m\n    elif block.type == [0m\"text[0m\":[0m\n        print(f[0m\"📝 Response: {block.text}[0m\")[0m\n```[0m\n[0m\n### Streaming with Thinking[0m\n[0m\n```python[0m\nwith client.messages.stream([0m\n    model=[0m\"claude-sonnet-4-20250514[0m\",[0m\n    max_tokens=1024,[0m\n    thinking={[0m\"type[0m\": [0m\"enabled[0m\", [0m\"budget_tokens[0m\": 200},[0m\n    messages=[{[0m\"role[0m\": [0m\"user[0m\", [0m\"content[0m\": [0m\"Explain quantum entanglement[0m\"}][0m\n) as stream:[0m\n    for event in stream:[0m\n        if hasattr(event, 'type'):[0m\n            if event.type == 'content_block_delta':[0m\n                if hasattr(event.delta, 'thinking'):[0m\n                    print(event.delta.thinking, end=[0m\"[0m\", flush=True)[0m\n                elif hasattr(event.delta, 'text'):[0m\n                    print(event.delta.text, end=[0m\"[0m\", flush=True)[0m\n```[0m\n[0m\n---[0m\n[0m\n## API Reference[0m\n[0m\n### Endpoints[0m\n[0m\n| Endpoint | Method | Description |[0m\n|----------|--------|-------------|[0m\n| `/v1/messages` | POST | Anthropic Messages API |[0m\n| `/anthropic/v1/messages` | POST | Alternative base path |[0m\n| `/api/v1/messages` | POST | Alternative base path |[0m\n| `/v1/chat/completions` | POST | OpenAI Chat API |[0m\n| `/v1/models` | GET | List available models |[0m\n| `/health` | GET | Health check |[0m\n| `/info` | GET | API information |[0m\n[0m\n### Request Format[0m\n[0m\n```bash[0m\ncurl -X POST https://your-server/v1/messages [0m\\[0m\n  -H [0m\"Content-Type: application/json[0m\" [0m\\[0m\n  -H [0m\"x-api-key: your-key[0m\" [0m\\[0m\n  -H [0m\"anthropic-version: 2023-06-01[0m\" [0m\\[0m\n  -d '{[0m\n    [0m\"model[0m\": [0m\"claude-sonnet-4-20250514[0m\",[0m\n    [0m\"max_tokens[0m\": 1024,[0m\n    [0m\"messages[0m\": [[0m\n      {[0m\"role[0m\": [0m\"user[0m\", [0m\"content[0m\": [0m\"Hello![0m\"}[0m\n    ][0m\n  }'[0m\n```[0m\n[0m\n### Response Format[0m\n[0m\n```json[0m\n{[0m\n  [0m\"id[0m\": [0m\"msg_abc123[0m\",[0m\n  [0m\"type[0m\": [0m\"message[0m\",[0m\n  [0m\"role[0m\": [0m\"assistant[0m\",[0m\n  [0m\"content[0m\": [[0m\n    {[0m\"type[0m\": [0m\"text[0m\", [0m\"text[0m\": [0m\"Hello! How can I help you today?[0m\"}[0m\n  ],[0m\n  [0m\"model[0m\": [0m\"claude-sonnet-4-20250514[0m\",[0m\n  [0m\"stop_reason[0m\": [0m\"end_turn[0m\",[0m\n  [0m\"usage[0m\": {[0m\n    [0m\"input_tokens[0m\": 10,[0m\n    [0m\"output_tokens[0m\": 25[0m\n  }[0m\n}[0m\n```[0m\n[0m\n### Supported Parameters[0m\n[0m\n| Parameter | Type | Description |[0m\n|-----------|------|-------------|[0m\n| `model` | string | Model identifier |[0m\n| `messages` | array | Conversation messages |[0m\n| `max_tokens` | integer | Maximum response tokens |[0m\n| `temperature` | float | Sampling temperature (0.0-1.0) |[0m\n| `top_p` | float | Nucleus sampling (0.0-1.0) |[0m\n| `stream` | boolean | Enable streaming |[0m\n| `system` | string | System prompt |[0m\n| `thinking` | object | Enable interleaved thinking |[0m\n| `tools` | array | Available tools |[0m\n| `tool_choice` | object | Tool selection preference |[0m\n[0m\n---[0m\n[0m\n## Deployment[0m\n[0m\n### HuggingFace Spaces (Recommended)[0m\n[0m\n```yaml[0m\n# README.md frontmatter[0m\n---[0m\ntitle: Docker Model Runner[0m\nemoji: 🚀[0m\ncolorFrom: blue[0m\ncolorTo: purple[0m\nsdk: docker[0m\napp_port: 7860[0m\nsuggested_hardware: cpu-basic[0m\n---[0m\n```[0m\n[0m\n### Docker Compose[0m\n[0m\n```yaml[0m\nversion: '3.8'[0m\nservices:[0m\n  model-runner:[0m\n    build: .[0m\n    ports:[0m\n      - [0m\"7860:7860[0m\"[0m\n    environment:[0m\n      - OMP_NUM_THREADS=2[0m\n      - MKL_NUM_THREADS=2[0m\n    deploy:[0m\n      resources:[0m\n        limits:[0m\n          cpus: '2'[0m\n          memory: 16G[0m\n```[0m\n[0m\n### Kubernetes[0m\n[0m\n```yaml[0m\napiVersion: apps/v1[0m\nkind: Deployment[0m\nmetadata:[0m\n  name: model-runner[0m\nspec:[0m\n  replicas: 1[0m\n  template:[0m\n    spec:[0m\n      containers:[0m\n      - name: model-runner[0m\n        image: your-registry/model-runner:latest[0m\n        ports:[0m\n        - containerPort: 7860[0m\n        resources:[0m\n          limits:[0m\n            cpu: [0m\"2[0m\"[0m\n            memory: [0m\"16Gi[0m\"[0m\n```[0m\n[0m\n---[0m\n[0m\n## Architecture[0m\n[0m\n```[0m\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐[0m\n│                    Docker Model Runner                       │[0m\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤[0m\n│                                                              │[0m\n│  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐       │[0m\n│  │   /v1/       │  │  /anthropic/ │  │  /api/v1/    │       │[0m\n│  │   messages   │  │  v1/messages │  │  messages    │       │[0m\n│  └──────┬───────┘  └──────┬───────┘  └──────┬───────┘       │[0m\n│         │                 │                  │               │[0m\n│         └─────────────────┼──────────────────┘               │[0m\n│                           ▼                                  │[0m\n│                 ┌──────────────────┐                         │[0m\n│                 │  Request Handler │                         │[0m\n│                 │  (FastAPI)       │                         │[0m\n│                 └────────┬─────────┘                         │[0m\n│                          │                                   │[0m\n│         ┌────────────────┼────────────────┐                  │[0m\n│         ▼                ▼                ▼                  │[0m\n│  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐          │[0m\n│  │   Thinking  │  │    Text     │  │    Tool     │          │[0m\n│  │  Generator  │  │  Generator  │  │   Handler   │          │[0m\n│  └─────────────┘  └─────────────┘  └─────────────┘          │[0m\n│                          │                                   │[0m\n│                          ▼                                   │[0m\n│                 ┌──────────────────┐                         │[0m\n│                 │  Transformers    │                         │[0m\n│                 │  (CPU Optimized) │                         │[0m\n│                 └──────────────────┘                         │[0m\n│                                                              │[0m\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘[0m\n```[0m\n[0m\n---[0m\n[0m\n## Configuration[0m\n[0m\n### Environment Variables[0m\n[0m\n| Variable | Default | Description |[0m\n|----------|---------|-------------|[0m\n| `GENERATOR_MODEL` | `distilgpt2` | Text generation model |[0m\n| `MODEL_NAME` | `MiniMax-M2` | Display model name |[0m\n| `OMP_NUM_THREADS` | `2` | OpenMP threads |[0m\n| `MKL_NUM_THREADS` | `2` | MKL threads |[0m\n[0m\n### Customizing Models[0m\n[0m\nEdit `main.py` to use different models:[0m\n[0m\n```python[0m\nGENERATOR_MODEL = os.getenv([0m\"GENERATOR_MODEL[0m\", [0m\"gpt2-medium[0m\")[0m\n```[0m\n[0m\n---[0m\n[0m\n## Performance[0m\n[0m\n| Metric | Value |[0m\n|--------|-------|[0m\n| Cold Start | ~30s |[0m\n| Inference Latency | 50-200ms/token |[0m\n| Memory Usage | ~4GB |[0m\n| Concurrent Requests | 5-10 |[0m\n[0m\n---[0m\n[0m\n## Contributing[0m\n[0m\nContributions are welcome! Please read our [Contributing Guide](CONTRIBUTING.md) first.[0m\n[0m\n1. Fork the repository[0m\n2. Create your feature branch (`git checkout -b feature/amazing-feature`)[0m\n3. Commit your changes (`git commit -m 'Add amazing feature'`)[0m\n4. Push to the branch (`git push origin feature/amazing-feature`)[0m\n5. Open a Pull Request[0m\n[0m\n---[0m\n[0m\n## License[0m\n[0m\nThis project is licensed under the MIT License - see the [LICENSE](LICENSE) file for details.[0m\n[0m\n---[0m\n[0m\n## Acknowledgements[0m\n[0m\n- [HuggingFace](https://huggingface.co) for Spaces and Transformers[0m\n- [Anthropic](https://anthropic.com) for the API specification[0m\n- [FastAPI](https://fastapi.tiangolo.com) for the web framework[0m\n[0m\n---[0m\n[0m\n<p align=[0m\"center[0m\">[0m\n  <strong>⭐ Star this repo if you find it useful!</strong>[0m\n</p>[0m\n[0m\n<p align=[0m\"center[0m\">[0m\n  Made with ❤️ by <a href=[0m\"https://github.com/likhonsheikhdev[0m\"><strong>Likhon Sheikh</strong></a>[0m\n</p>[0m\n[0m\n<p align=[0m\"center[0m\">[0m\n  <a href=[0m\"https://github.com/likhonsheikhdev[0m\">[0m\n    <img src=[0m\"https://img.shields.io/badge/GitHub-likhonsheikhdev-181717?style=for-the-badge&logo=github[0m\" alt=[0m\"GitHub[0m\">[0m\n  </a>[0m\n  <a href=[0m\"https://t.me/likhonsheikh[0m\">[0m\n    <img src=[0m\"https://img.shields.io/badge/Telegram-@likhonsheikh-2CA5E0?style=for-the-badge&logo=telegram[0m\" alt=[0m\"Telegram[0m\">[0m\n  </a>[0m\n</p>[0m\n[0m\n---[0m\n[0m\n## Contact & Support[0m\n[0m\n| Ch